itten by Epstein, not credible reporting that questions whether he wrote it.\n\nThe standard of proof is preponderance—more likely than not. Given that multiple mainstream outlets reported on the document while consistently noting unverified authorship, an unsigned note, and lack of authentication, the reporting actually preserves doubt rather than resolving it. The proposition demands that credible reporting establish Epstein's authorship, but the record shows credible reporting that explicitly does not establish it.\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning","type":"thinking"},{"text":" the deliberation prompt","type":"text"}],"model":"qwen/qwen3.5-plus-02-15","provider":"openrouter","responseId":"gen-1782794799-4Er2tIw7lR0r3cDCnHKe","responseModel":"qwen/qwen3.5-plus-20260216","role":"assistant","stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1782794799018,"usage":{"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"cost":{"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"input":0,"output":0,"total":0},"input":0,"output":0,"totalTokens":0}},"type":"message_update"}
