gSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"I have reviewed the deliberation prompt and admitted evidence. Let me examine the case record to ensure I have a complete understanding of the evidence before voting.\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_fe921eba4c9b457284b0b1f9","name":"mcp","arguments":{"tool":"aar_get_case"},"partialArgs":"{\"tool\": \"aar_get_case","streamIndex":0}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"qwen/qwen3.5-plus-02-15","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1782794799018,"responseId":"gen-1782794799-4Er2tIw7lR0r3cDCnHKe","responseModel":"qwen/qwen3.5-plus-20260216"}},"message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I'm council member C3 in deliberation round 1. The proposition is:\n\n\"By May 8, 2026, 11:59 PM ET, a message or note credibly reported to have been written by Jeffrey Epstein and intended as a suicide note, final message, or equivalent communication had been made publicly available.\"\n\nStandard of evidence: Preponderance of the evidence.\n\nLet me review the admitted record:\n\n**Key Evidence:**\n\n1. **PX-1 (Market Rule)**: The market resolves \"Yes\" if any message/note written by Epstein, intended as a suicide note, is made publicly available by the date. Resolution source is \"consensus of credible reporting.\"\n\n2. **PX-4 (SDNY Order)**: Official court document showing Judge Karas granted the Times' request to unseal \"an alleged 'suicide note purportedly authored by Jeffrey Epstein, recovered by...Tartaglione, and then reportedly submitted by...Tartaglione's attorneys.'\" The order is about public access, not authentication.\n\n3. **PX-5 (Reuters Connect)**: Image caption metadata describing \"a document including the line 'It is a treat to be able to choose one's time to say goodbye.', described as a suicide note purportedly written by th