hat the note was \"written by Jeffrey Epstein and intended as a suicide note/final message.\" The unanimous pattern across all credible sources is to report the note as \"alleged\" or \"purported\" while explicitly preserving uncertainty about authorship (DOJ never had it, not authenticated, first time seeing it, unclear who wrote it, no signature). This is not credible reporting that establishes authorship by a preponderance—it is credible reporting that expressly documents unresolved authorship questions.\n\nThe defense position is correct: the record proves public availability of a disputed document, but not the full proposition that a note was credibly reported to have been written by Epstein and intended as a qualifying communication.\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_17dcd4a3b8fc454f9c68fb0f","name":"mcp","arguments":{"tool":"aar_submit_council_vote","args":"{\"vote\":\"not"},"partialArgs":"{\"tool\": \"aar_submit_council_vote\", \"args\": \"{\\\"vote\\\":\\\"not","streamIndex":0}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"qwen/qwen3.5-plus-02-15","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1782794816471,"responseId":"gen-1782794816-8HrfuoHD6p9C6dPtnixl","responseModel":"qwen/qwen3.5-plus-20260216"}},"message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I have now reviewed the complete case record. The proposition is:\n\n**\"By May 8, 2026, 11:59 PM ET, a message or note credibly reported to have been written by Jeffrey Epstein and intended as a suicide note, final message, or equivalent communication had been made publicly available.\"**\n\nThe standard is preponderance of the evidence, with resolution by consensus of credible reporting.\n\n**Key observations from the admitted record:**\n\n1. **Public availability**: Uncontested. The SDNY order (PX-4/DB-2) shows Judge Karas granted access to the not